"title": "8024: faith, and blessings of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8024",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Confidence in the ability and willingness of God to act in supernatural power to advance his kingdom, and a commitment, expressed in prayer and action, to being the means by which he does so.</p>\n<h2>God's power is released through faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:20\">MAT 17:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:23\">MRK 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:6\">LUK 17:6</a></p>\n<h3>Praying in faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:21-Matt21:22\">MAT 21:21–21:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:22-Mark11:24\">MRK 11:22–11:24</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:5-Jas1:7\">JAS 1:5–1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14-Jas5:15\">JAS 5:14–5:15</a></p>\n<h3>Praying in Jesus Christ's name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:12-John14:14\">JHN 14:12–14:14</a></strong></p>\n<h2>In the OT, faith in God's power</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:32-Heb11:34\">HEB 11:32–11:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:11-Heb11:12\">HEB 11:11–11:12</a> <em>Abraham's faith when promised an heir in his old age</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:6-Josh14:14\">JOS 14:6–14:14</a> <em>Caleb receives Hebron</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:6\">1SA 14:6</a> <em>Jonathan's confidence in God's power to defeat the Philistines</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:32-1Sam17:47\">1SA 17:32–17:47</a> <em>David's confidence in God's power to overcome Goliath</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:20\">2CH 20:20</a> <em>Jehoshaphat's faith in God's power to give success against Moab and Ammon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:7-2Chr32:8\">2CH 32:7–32:8</a> <em>Hezekiah's faith in God when threatened by the Assyrians under Sennacherib</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:23\">DAN 6:23</a> <em>Daniel's faith when in the lions' den</em></p>\n<h2>In the NT, healing in response to faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:22\">MAT 9:22</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:34\">MRK 5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:48\">LUK 8:48</a> <em>The woman had exercised faith by touching the edge of Jesus Christ's cloak.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:29-Matt9:30\">MAT 9:29–9:30</a> <em>Two blind men are healed</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:52\">MRK 10:52</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:42\">LUK 18:42</a> <em>Bartimaeus receives his sight</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:19\">LUK 17:19</a> <em>One of the ten men with leprosy who thanked Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:16\">ACT 3:16</a> <em>the crippled man at the temple gate</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:8-Acts14:10\">ACT 14:8–14:10</a> <em>the crippled man in Lystra</em></p>\n<h2>Powerful ministries marked by faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:24\">ACT 11:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:5-Acts6:10\">ACT 6:5–6:10</a> <em>Stephen</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:9\">1CO 12:9</a> <em>Exceptional faith to meet specific needs is a special spiritual gift.</em></p>\n<h2>Faith and spiritual warfare</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:16\">EPH 6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:8\">1TH 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:4-1John5:5\">1JN 5:4–5:5</a></p>\n<h2>The importance of love accompanying faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:2\">1CO 13:2</a></strong></p>",
